descript.abstract: The Virginia Geographic Information Network (VGIN) has coordinated the development of a consistent, seamless, statewide digital road centerline file with address, road name, and route number attribution, as part of the Virginia Base Mapping Program (VBMP). The Road Centerline Program (RCL) leverages the Commonwealth's investment in the VBMP digital orthophotography and is focused on creating a single statewide, consistent digital road file. The RCL data layer is a dynamic dataset supported and maintained by Virginia's Local Governments and VGIN. VBMP RCL is extracted and provided back to local governments and state agencies in many geographic data sets every quarter. Please note the following use restrictions: RCL Geometry is public domain; Minimal Attribution is public domain (RCL Public); Geocoding fields are restricted in use (RCL Master) and to acquire these, please contact VGIN.
descript.purpose: The ongoing goal of the VBMP is to establish a consistent, seamless base and foundation for local and state government mapping systems (GIS) that will help all increase efficiency and reduce redundant efforts in developing these systems. The seamless VBMP base is critical to the effective and efficient delivery of wireless E-911 and many other government services and is a critical component in the development of spatial data guidelines and standards, supporting the cost-effective sharing of GIS data and expertise across the Commonwealth.

dataLineage.statement: The descriptions used for lineage are to represent basic functions in maintenance and preparation of data. Database is housed in a SQL server in conjunction with SDE. All deltas, QC, and geoprocessing are done in separate file and personal database environments and changes are applied to RCL master database as needed.

RCL_ID values that were 0 or duplicates were calculated based on a post processing script. This processing routine is run as needed. FIPS_SEGMENT values that were NULL or miscalculated during editing process were assigned FIPS codes from the Provider Management Boundary (PMB) using a geoprocessing model. The location of the line segment centroid determined the FIPS assignment.

RCL post process geoprocessing model was run for ZIP_LEFT and ZIP_RIGHT. Fields were calculated by using VGIN's custom zip code polygon boundary and using select by location using the centroid of the line segment within the polygon boundary.

GEO_ID field populated for the purpose of a providing a unique GEOID for each segment. Calculation is based upon the concatenation of a rounded X and Y Lambert coordinate, providing negative and positive numerical association. This field is maintained with post process scripting in a related table creates new GEOIDs for null and duplicate records based on edit code and date.
